  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package carries the targeted W-EP-03 weakness: the primary experimental dataset (FDA pump PIV/hemolysis campaign) carries a dataVintage of 2025-09-04T00:00:00Z, which predates the modelRevisionDate of 2025-09-25T00:00:00Z by three weeks. The revision incorporated updated impeller tip-clearance geometry and revised viscosity sub-model coefficients. The assessment narrative argues the change was 'not material' to the experimental dataset's relevance; however, no formal re-validation against the revised model build was performed, leaving an unresolved stale-data epistemic gap.",
  "modelRevisionDate": "2025-09-25T00:00:00Z",
